data.subsequentPremium: Additional purchase payments made after the rider effective date will increase the protected payment base by the amount of the Purchase Payments.
data.partialWithdrawals: withdraw more than the protected payment amount in a contract year, your protected payment base may be reduced on a proportionate basis for the amount withdrawn in excess of your protected payment amount.
data.reqdMinDistributions: RMD withdrawals exceeding the Protected Payment Amount will not be treated as excess withdrawals and have no effect on Protected Payment Base.
data.benefitDescription: The rider focus on providing an income stream for life through withdrawals during the accumulation phase, even if the contract value is reduced to zero. It also offers the potential to lock in market gains on each contract anniversary which are used to calculate annual rider withdrawal limits.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: Protected Payment Amount is the amount that can be withdrawn under the rider, which depends on the age of the designated life, If the Designated Life is younger than 59 years of age, the Protected Payment Amount is equal to zero. the Protected Payment Amount is the Withdrawal Percentage multiplied by the Protected Payment Base, less Withdrawals made during the Contract Year. Protected payment base is determined on the basis of Annual Credit Value. Initial Protected Payment Base is equal to the initial Purchase Payment. the Annual Credit amount is equal to the reset Protected Payment Base plus any subsequent Purchase Payments multiplied by the Annual Credit Percentage. On each contract anniversary, it is until the earlier of 1) the first withdrawal since the Rider Effective Date, or 2) 10 Contract Anniversaries from the Rider Effective Date.
data.benefitBaseNoWithdrawal: If no withdrawals are made for the first 10 years from the rider effective date, the Protected Payment Base will be increased by the Annual Credit amount.
data.benefitBaseWithdrawal: The Protected Payment Amount will be reduced by the amount withdrawn during the Contract Year, inclusive of any applicable charges and taxes, and will be reset each Contract Anniversary. Any portion of the Protected Payment Amount not withdrawn during a Contract Year may not be carried over to the next Contract Year. If a withdrawal does not exceed the Protected Payment Amount immediately prior to that withdrawal, the Protected Payment Base will remain unchanged. If owner takes any type of withdrawal within the first 10 years from the Rider Effective Date, the Annual Credit will no longer affect the Protected Payment Base.
data.notes: Rider not available for Inherited IRA, Inherited Roth IRA, Inherited TSA, or Non-Qualified Stretch. Joint owners are not permitted on the single life version of the rider. Additional plan types not allowed for joint life are 401(a), 401(k), Individual (k), Keogh, 457 plans.
data.withdrawalNotes: Lifetime Withdrawal Percentages are based on the age of the Designated Life at the time the first withdrawal.
data.chargeNotes: The quarterly charge is  of the Annual Charge Percentage multiplied by the Protected Payment Base.
data.initialResetText: On each Contract Anniversary, while this Rider is in effect and before the Annuity Date, we will automatically reset the Protected Payment Base to an amount equal to 100% of the Contract Value, if the Protected Payment Base, after any Annual Credit is applied, is at least $1.00 less than the Contract Value on that Contract Anniversary.
data.restrictionOnSubAcctNotes: Owner May allocate Contract Value 100% among the allowable Investment Options.

data.partialWithdrawals: If withdrawal exceeds the protected payment amount immediately prior to that withdrawal, it reduce the Protected Payment Base on a proportionate basis for the amount in excess of the protected payment amount. It will reduce the remaining protected balance either on a proportionate basis or by the total withdrawal amount, whichever results in the lower remaining protected balance amount.
data.reqdMinDistributions: RMD withdrawals exceeding the Protected Payment Amount will not be treated as excess withdrawals and have no effect on Protected Payment Base.
data.benefitDescription: This rider provides a guaranteed lifetime withdrawal benefit. The guaranteed minimum withdrawal benefit rider provides lifetime income stream through withdrawals during the accumulation phase if certain conditions are met.
data.benefitBaseGeneral: The Protected Payment Base is equal to the initial purchase payment, if the rider effective date is on the contract date; or the contract value, if the rider effective date is on any date rather than contract date. Protected Payment Amount is the maximum amount that can be withdrawn under the rider without reducing the Protected Payment Base and will never be less than zero. This rider provides an automatic reset of the Protected Payment Base to an amount equal to 100% of the contract value, if the Protected Payment Base is less than the Contract Value on that Contract Anniversary.
data.benefitBaseWithdrawal: The Protected Payment Amount will be reduced by the amount withdrawn during the Contract Year and will be reset each Contract Anniversary to 5.6% (5% for joint life) of the Protected Payment Base. Any portion of the Protected Payment Amount not withdrawn during a Contract Year may not be carried over to the next Contract Year. If a withdrawal does not exceed the Protected Payment Amount immediately prior to that withdrawal, the Protected Payment Base will remain unchanged
data.notes: Rider is issued as Single Life and Joint Life versions. Owner may elect only one of the version at any time. Rider is not issued for Inherited IRA, Inherited Roth IRA or Inherited TSA. For joint life, in addition to the above plan types, non-qualified contracts are not available for non natural owners. Issuer applies max charge as per the 10-year treasury rate monthly rate 1.00% for monthly average 4.00%, 1.50% for monthly average 2.00% to 3.99% and 2.00% for monthly average less than 2.00%; for single life and for joint life 1.50% for monthly average 4.00%, 2.00% for monthly average 2.00% to 3.99% and 2.50% for monthly average less than 2.00%.
data.chargeNotes: Current charge for this rider is based on the 10-Year Treasury Rate (the monthly average as published by the Federal Reserve) and will not exceed the maximum charge. Annual charge is equal to the current charge percentage multiplied by the Protected Payment Base, deducted on a quarterly basis.
data.initialResetText: On each contract anniversary while this rider is in effect and before the annuity date, Issuer will automatically reset the protected payment base to an amount equal to 100% of contract value, if the protected payment base is at least $1.00 less than the contract value on that contract anniversary.
data.feeOption: Initial annual charge percentage is guaranteed not to change until the 1st contract anniversary. Any increase in the annual charge percentage will not exceed 0.50% from the previous contract year.

data.otherAnnuityOption: Single/Joint Life with Cash Refund and Installment refund (fixed only), Joint life with period certain of 5-30 years (fixed or variable).
data.notes: Default Annuity option with Non-Qualified contract is Life with 10 Years period and Qualified contract is Life with 5 Years or less period. If net amount is less than $10,000, entire amount will be distributed in one lump sum. Owner may choose annuity payments made monthly, quarterly, semi-annually or annually and initial annuity payment must be at least $250.
